我们无条件的救了贝尔斯登 又无条件的救了美国国际集团
We rescued Bear with no legislation, AIG with no legislation.

1088
01:01:36,526 --> 01:01:38,778
人们会认为房利美和房地美在诱售
People think Fannie and Freddie was a bait-and-switch.

1089
01:01:38,862 --> 01:01:42,365
你以为我愿意这样做吗 但是他们的状况都很特殊
I don't like it any more than you do, but they were exceptional situations.

1090
01:01:42,449 --> 01:01:45,451
现在的情况要求
This situation demands an endgame

1091
01:01:45,535 --> 01:01:48,913
那些公司不能再依靠联邦政府的协助
that does not rely on unilateral action from the Fed.

1092
01:01:48,997 --> 01:01:50,331
这才是民主
This is a democracy.

1093
01:01:50,415 --> 01:01:52,958
我们不能垂帘听政在幕后操纵
We cannot be men behind the curtain pulling the strings.

1094
01:01:53,293 --> 01:01:57,671
我们需要找到一个完善的解决方法来修复整个金融体系
We need some kind of an overall solution that heals the entire system.

1095
01:01:57,756 --> 01:01:59,715
并且是通过合法的方式进行
And it has to be legitimate.

1096
01:01:59,800 --> 01:02:01,342
我们一再推迟了向国会汇报这些事情
We've been putting off going to Congress.

1097
01:02:01,426 --> 01:02:03,094
离大选只有两个月了
It's two months before an election.

1098
01:02:03,178 --> 01:02:08,891
选民们不可能投票给一个使得整个银行系统崩溃的政府
They can't vote yes to a massive bailout of the entire banking system.

1099
01:02:08,975 --> 01:02:10,434
- 选民们不可能再选择我们  - Hank...
- They'd never get reelected.  - Hank...

1100
01:02:10,644 --> 01:02:14,438
我们去国会说清楚我们已经对现在的局势
We go to Congress, publically state we don't have the firepower

1101
01:02:14,523 --> 01:02:18,567
无能为力了 但是他们说不行
to control this anymore, and then they say no,

1102
01:02:19,528 --> 01:02:22,988
这种场景真是一场噩梦
that is really the nightmare scenario.

1103
01:02:23,532 --> 01:02:26,826
噩梦场景已经出现了 我的朋友
The nightmare scenario's already here, my friend.

1104
01:02:27,744 --> 01:02:29,245
而且我们深陷其中
We're in it.

1105
01:03:30,682 --> 01:03:32,057
P你还好吗
P.

1106
01:03:43,695 --> 01:03:45,738
你不能把所有事情都自己扛下来
You can't put this all on your own shoulders.

1107
01:03:45,822 --> 01:03:47,156
我们已经别无选择了
We're running out of options.

1108
01:03:48,742 --> 01:03:51,994
那么你就继续尝试别的方法 这才是你该做的
Then you just keep trying. That's what you do.

1109
01:03:52,078 --> 01:03:54,079
最后肯定会有办法解决的
Eventually something's gonna work.

1110
01:03:54,164 --> 01:03:56,916
我都不知道 是不是这样的了
I'm not sure that that is true anymore.

1111
01:03:58,001 --> 01:04:01,587
但是这世界上没有一家银行是有足够的钱去应对
There's not a bank in the world that has enough money in its vault

1112
01:04:01,671 --> 01:04:05,758
储户的提款要求 银行都是建立在信用基础上的
to pay its depositors. It's all built on trust.

1113
01:04:05,842 --> 01:04:11,430
而且 Wendy 我们已经岌岌可危了
And, Wendy, we are so very close.

1114
01:04:14,726 --> 01:04:18,395
摩根斯坦利 高盛已经在悬崖边缘
Morgan Stanley, Goldman are an inch away.

1115
01:04:18,480 --> 01:04:24,026
如果别的银行不再信任他们 如果他们停止了银行间的拆借
If the other banks stop trusting them, if they pull back on interbank lending,

1116
01:04:24,110 --> 01:04:26,445
他们会立刻破产
it's over in a matter of hours.

1117
01:04:27,113 --> 01:04:31,200
而且一旦破产开始了就不会停下来 会有连锁反应
And from there it goes too fast to stop, a run,

1118
01:04:31,284 --> 01:04:36,247
而且到时候破产的就不仅仅是银行了 整个金融系统都会崩塌
and not just on one bank, I mean on the whole system.

1119
01:04:36,331 --> 01:04:40,376
然后大众就会问 "我的钱安全吗?" 
And average people wondering, "Is my money safe?"

1120
01:04:41,628 --> 01:04:43,963
他们开始提现
They start pulling their cash.

1121
01:04:46,132 --> 01:04:50,636
再然后 银行门口就会排起长队 ATM机就会被挤爆
And after that, lines outside the banks, smashed ATMs.

1122
01:04:51,638 --> 01:04:53,472
再过几个星期
A couple of weeks,

1123
01:04:54,975 --> 01:04:57,351
银行里就没有钱可以提了
there's no milk in the store.

1124
01:04:58,311 --> 01:04:59,520
这已经是本周第二次
For the second time this week,

1125
01:04:59,604 --> 01:05:01,564
华尔街出现了大量的抛售
there was a massive sell-off on Wall Street,

1126
01:05:01,648 --> 01:05:05,025
道琼斯工业指数暴跌超过450点
the Dow Jones Industrial's freefalling some 450 points

1127
01:05:05,110 --> 01:05:09,321
因为消息称纳税人的资金用来救援美国国际集团保险公司
on news of a taxpayer-funded bailout of the AIG insurance company.

1128
01:05:09,406 --> 01:05:11,490
五大投行中三家已经倒闭了
Three of the five investment banks are gone.

1129
01:05:11,575 --> 01:05:13,909
全国最大的抵押贷款机构也倒闭了
The country's biggest mortgage lender is gone.

1130
01:05:13,994 --> 01:05:16,704
房利美 房地美也已经收归国有
Fannie Mae, Freddie Mac, brought under government control.

1131
01:05:16,788 --> 01:05:20,499
金融系统现在算是保住了 但是能维持多久?
The financial system is holding right now, but for how long?

1132
01:05:20,834 --> 01:05:22,960
全部人力 全部资源都被完全利用
All the king's horses and all the king's men

1133
01:05:23,044 --> 01:05:25,087
一定保持金融体系的顺利运行
are being brought to bear to keep this thing together.

1134
01:05:52,240 --> 01:05:54,533
- 嗨 Tim  - 我在华尔街 Hank
- Hi, Tim.  - I'm on the Street, Hank,

1135
01:05:54,618 --> 01:05:57,286
人们正要赶着去上班
and people are just going about their business.

1136
01:05:57,370 --> 01:06:01,081
他们完全不知道这里的一切都将化为乌有
They have no idea the whole thing is about to fall down.

1137
01:06:02,000 --> 01:06:05,628
我们不得不向国会报告了 我们已经别无选择
We're gonna have to go to Congress. We don't have a choice anymore.

1138
01:06:05,712 --> 01:06:06,837
好吧
Okay.

1139
01:06:06,921 --> 01:06:08,464
你觉得还要多久他们会做出决定?
How fast do you think you can get them to move?

1140
01:06:08,548 --> 01:06:10,716
我想至少也要几天
It's gonna be at least a couple days.

1141
01:06:11,301 --> 01:06:14,178
高盛和摩根斯坦利已经快不行了 
Goldman and Morgan Stanley are going down now.

1142
01:06:14,262 --> 01:06:15,638
我们今天必须做点什么
We gotta do something today.

1143
01:06:15,722 --> 01:06:16,847
比如说?
Like what?

1144
01:06:16,931 --> 01:06:19,475
市场不像投行一样 对吗?
The market doesn't like investment banks, right?

1145
01:06:19,559 --> 01:06:21,769
所有的商业模型都拿那些钱束手无策 
The money's saying "fuck you" to the whole business model.

1146
01:06:21,853 --> 01:06:22,895
是的
Yeah.

1147
01:06:22,979 --> 01:06:26,065
是的 那让他们变成商业银行
Yeah, so merge them with commercial banks,

1148
01:06:26,149 --> 01:06:28,651
把投行变成普通的由联邦政府监管的商业银行
turn them into regular banks regulated by the Fed.

1149
01:06:28,735 --> 01:06:30,152
他们就能动用储户的钱了
They can use depositors' cash.

1150
01:06:30,236 --> 01:06:31,862
这样他们就能通过贴现窗口
It will give them access to the discount window.

1151
01:06:31,946 --> 01:06:34,990
向政府以较低的利率借款
It's cheap government cash.

1152
01:06:35,075 --> 01:06:37,826
- 你想让他们变得更大吗?  - 这也是没办法的办法 Hank
- You wanna make them bigger?  - It's a trade-off, Hank.

1153
01:06:37,911 --> 01:06:40,954
好处是他们可以逐渐稳定下来
The upside is it'll stabilize them.

1154
01:06:42,374 --> 01:06:44,583
坏处是
The downside is,

1155
01:06:45,585 --> 01:06:48,337
对的 他们会变得出奇的庞大
yeah, they'll be really fucking big.

1156
01:06:48,421 --> 01:06:50,005
去做吧 Tim
Do it, Tim.

1157
01:06:52,967 --> 01:06:54,259
快去做
Godspeed.

1158
01:07:12,028 --> 01:07:14,196
嗯 给我接Blankfein
Uh, get me Blankfein.

1159
01:07:16,116 --> 01:07:18,117
Lloyd 打电话给Vikram Pandit 告诉他你想合并
Lloyd, call Vikram Pandit, talk to him about a merger.

1160
01:07:18,201 --> 01:07:20,244
Tim 我们正在尽全力想办法
Tim, we're looking at all our options.

1161
01:07:20,370 --> 01:07:23,872
你已经走投无路了 Lloyd 你的银行只能这样做
You don't have options, Lloyd. There's a run on your bank.

1162
01:07:23,957 --> 01:07:25,582
你需要钱 花旗又有存款
You need money. Citi has deposits.

1163
01:07:25,667 --> 01:07:28,335
花旗现在一团糟 你这里有条不紊 打电话给Pandit
Citi's a mess, you're organized. Call Pandit.

1164
01:07:37,762 --> 01:07:38,804
怎么了
Yeah.

1165
01:07:38,888 --> 01:07:40,848
我希望你可以考虑考虑和摩根斯坦利合并
I want you to look at merging with Morgan Stanley.

1166
01:07:40,932 --> 01:07:43,058
什么 你在开玩笑吧? 我刚刚买了贝尔斯登
What, are you kidding me? I just bought Bear.

1167
01:07:43,143 --> 01:07:44,518
我们仍然在想办法让它开始好转
We're still trying to make that work.

1168
01:07:44,602 --> 01:07:46,395
你没有买贝尔斯登 它几乎算是送你的
You didn't buy Bear. You got Bear as a Christmas present.

1169
01:07:46,479 --> 01:07:50,649
市场现在一团糟 Jamie 跟John Mack聊聊
The market's a fucking disaster, Jamie. Talk to John Mack.

1170
01:07:50,734 --> 01:07:53,610
嘿 Geithner说我们可以谈谈合并的事情
Hey, Geithner says we should talk about a merger.

1171
01:07:53,695 --> 01:07:55,529
- 你想这样做吗?  - 当然不想
- You wanna do a deal?  - No.

1172
01:07:55,613 --> 01:07:57,698
那他为什么要让我打给你?
Then why the fuck did he tell me to call you?

1173
01:07:57,782 --> 01:07:59,867
我得到命令去帮助你们公司
I'm under orders to try and help you.

1174
01:07:59,993 --> 01:08:03,078
你是个王子 Jamie 真的是王子
You're a prince, Jamie. A real prince.

1175
01:08:07,000 --> 01:08:11,503
很显然 有人认为把我们的公司进行合并是一个不错的方法
Apparently, some people seem to think combining our firms would be a good idea.

1176
01:08:11,713 --> 01:08:14,381
我想说我对于这通电话受宠若惊
I want you to know I'm flattered by this call.

1177
01:08:14,924 --> 01:08:18,677
Vikram 我没有奉承你的意思 相信我
Vikram, I'm not trying to flatter you, believe me.

1178
01:08:18,762 --> 01:08:20,262
Geithener打电话来了
Geithner's calling.

1179
01:08:20,346 --> 01:08:22,931
一摊子破事
Here comes goddamn eHarmony.

1180
01:08:23,016 --> 01:08:24,975
嘿 猜猜看 Jamie一点都不感兴趣
Hey, guess what. Jamie's not interested.

1181
01:08:28,146 --> 01:08:29,271
试试Wachovia
Do Wachovia.

1182
01:08:29,355 --> 01:08:31,315
他们是闭着眼睛进行抵押贷款买卖的
They were writing mortgages with their eyes closed.

1183
01:08:31,399 --> 01:08:33,442
Tim 那只是一块垃圾三明治 忘了他吧
Tim, it's a shit sandwich. Forget it.

1184
01:08:39,365 --> 01:08:41,283
我在四小时之内是赶不到你那边的
I haven't been able to reach you for four hours.

1185
01:08:41,367 --> 01:08:44,787
这在今天这样的日子里肯定是做不到的
That is totally fucking unacceptable on a day like today.

1186
01:08:45,038 --> 01:08:48,081
我不得不让我的公司去评估高盛合并事宜
I had to run my team through the Goldman proposal.

1187
01:08:48,166 --> 01:08:49,458
没用的
It's not gonna work.

1188
01:08:50,335 --> 01:08:52,878
你已经联系好高盛了 却没给我说一声?
You passed on Goldman without even talking to me?

1189
01:08:53,046 --> 01:08:55,881
我不需要在我的资产负债表上多出1兆亿的美元
I don't need another trillion dollars on my balance sheet.

1190
01:08:59,677 --> 01:09:03,722
下次我打给你的时候 记得接电话
Next time I call, pick up.

1191
01:09:05,350 --> 01:09:06,850
去死吧
Fucker.

1192
01:09:07,101 --> 01:09:10,479
问题就在于那些不良资产 我们把他们买过来就好了
The problem is the toxic assets. Let's just buy them.

1193
01:09:10,563 --> 01:09:12,397
哦 可以称为现金换垃圾
Ooh. We'll call it Cash for Trash.

1194
01:09:12,565 --> 01:09:15,067
当市场稳定下来了 我们再把这些垃圾倾销掉
When the market stabilizes, we'll unload them.

1195
01:09:15,151 --> 01:09:17,194
希望是这样 财政部能够把这些钱讨回来
Hopefully, Treasury will get its money back.

1196
01:09:17,278 --> 01:09:19,738
- 这是破杯计划的一部分吗?  - 基本上是
- Is that in the Break the Glass plan?  - Basically.

1197
01:09:19,823 --> 01:09:22,741
我的这份是不是少了几页 有谁能告诉我余下的几页...
My copy's missing some pages. Could someone else show me the rest of...

1198
01:09:22,826 --> 01:09:24,493
这个是简洁版
It's succinct.

1199
01:09:25,203 --> 01:09:27,663
我们在国会只有一次机会
We've got one shot with Congress.

1200
01:09:27,747 --> 01:09:31,291
你觉得国会会根据这三页纸就签署一份法案吗?
You want them to write a piece of legislation based on three pages?

1201
01:09:31,376 --> 01:09:32,417
听着 朋友们
Look, guys,

1202
01:09:32,794 --> 01:09:35,128
购买不良资产肯定是一个噩梦
buying toxic assets is gonna be a nightmare.

1203
01:09:35,213 --> 01:09:36,505
没人知道这些东西到底值几个子
Nobody knows what the stuff's worth.

1204
01:09:36,589 --> 01:09:39,341
也许这些不良资产永远都理不清 银行马上就要倒闭了
It'll take forever to untangle. These banks are going down now.

1205
01:09:39,425 --> 01:09:40,509
那我们能怎么做?
So what do we do?

1206
01:09:40,593 --> 01:09:43,929
你想要让信用市场继续运作 是吗? 你希望银行能够继续放贷?
You wanna unfreeze credit, right? You want the banks to lend people money?

1207
01:09:44,013 --> 01:09:46,682
- 这就是我们想要看到的  - 那就给他们钱让他们放贷
- That's the goal.  - So give them money to lend.

1208
01:09:49,811 --> 01:09:51,144
资产注入?
Capital injections?

1209
01:09:51,229 --> 01:09:52,271
Dan 摆脱别说傻话
Dan, come on.

1210
01:09:52,355 --> 01:09:53,856
我不相信你竟然说出了那个带 "N" 的字眼
I can't believe you're pulling out the "N" word.

1211
01:09:53,940 --> 01:09:55,148
我没有说要将银行国有化
I'm not saying nationalize the banks.

1212
01:09:55,233 --> 01:09:58,569
我说的是把有问题的银行隔离开 然后进行注资
I'm saying isolate the ones that are really in trouble and make an investment.

1213
01:09:58,653 --> 01:10:01,864
- 这做法不是美国人做的  - 当然也不是共和党人做的
- It's un-American.  - It's sure un-Republican.

1214
01:10:01,948 --> 01:10:05,200
你让政府变成了一个股东
You'd make the government a stockholder.

1215
01:10:05,285 --> 01:10:08,996
什么 我们是不是需要告诉他们怎么去经营 买哪些卖哪些?
What, do we tell them how to manage themselves, what to buy and sell?

1216
01:10:09,080 --> 01:10:11,957
像经营邮局一样经营他们? 是那样就太好了
Run them like the post office? 'Cause that works like a dream.

1217
01:10:12,041 --> 01:10:15,961
这只是暂时措施 我们可以是没有投票权的股东
We make it temporary. We make ourselves non-voting stockholders.

1218
01:10:16,170 --> 01:10:19,381
你不能捧着一叠叠的钞票送到银行里
You can't just hand the banks massive piles of cash.

1219
01:10:19,465 --> 01:10:21,049
没人会去理会这些的
Nobody's gonna go for it.

1220
01:10:21,134 --> 01:10:25,012
对于共和党来说这是资产国有化 对于民主党来说这就是救助
To the Republicans it's nationalization. To the Democrats it's a bailout.

1221
01:10:25,096 --> 01:10:26,680
而且银行会很生气的
And the banks are gonna go ballistic.

1222
01:10:26,848 --> 01:10:31,810
抱歉 Dan 这是不可能的 很欣赏你的创造性思维
Sorry, Dan, not gonna happen. Kudos for out-of-the-box thinking.

1223
01:10:31,895 --> 01:10:35,314
Neel 如果我们实行你的计划购买那些资产
Neel, if we go with your plan to buy the assets,

1224
01:10:35,398 --> 01:10:36,565
我们会花多少钱?
how much is it gonna cost?

1225
01:10:36,649 --> 01:10:38,025
那是不可能的
It won't work.

1226
01:10:38,109 --> 01:10:41,612
听着 计划只有3页长 而且很空洞
Look, the plan is three pages long, totally vague.

1227
01:10:41,696 --> 01:10:46,074
如果购买资产没有用的话 我们会用你的国有化计划 好吗?
If buying the assets doesn't work, we'll nationalize the banks for you, okay?

1228
01:10:46,326 --> 01:10:50,120
- 要多少钱?  - 保守估计 需要一万亿
- How much? - To be safe, maybe a trillion.

1229
01:10:50,830 --> 01:10:53,373
国会是不会批准一万亿的法案的 永远不会
The Congress will never do a trillion, never.

1230
01:10:53,541 --> 01:10:57,044
有11万亿美元的住房抵押债券
There's $11 trillion in residential mortgages.

1231
01:10:57,128 --> 01:11:02,424
还有三万亿的商业债券 一共是十四万亿 对吗?
There's three trillion in commercial mortgages. That's 14 trillion, right?

1232
01:11:02,508 --> 01:11:05,552
别忘了5%的违约率
You gotta figure about 5% default rate.

1233
01:11:06,512 --> 01:11:09,139
14万亿的5%是
5 % of 14 trillion is

1234
01:11:10,266 --> 01:11:12,225
七千万美元
$700 billion.

1235
01:11:15,521 --> 01:11:17,773
这也比一万亿要好
It's better than a trillion.

1236
01:11:21,444 --> 01:11:24,738
让法案通过的唯一方法只能是吓得他们屁滚尿流
The only way to get this done is to just scare them shitless.

1237
01:11:24,822 --> 01:11:28,033
这很简单 我自己都吓傻了
That should be easy. I'm scared shitless myself.

1238
01:11:24,822 --> 01:11:28,033
2008年9月18日 星期四 雷曼兄弟破产后三天

1239
01:11:40,047 --> 01:11:43,382
Barney Frank(马萨诸塞州代表) 众议院金融管理委员会主席

1240
01:11:41,047 --> 01:11:43,382
问题资产剥离计划?
Troubled Asset Relief Program?

1241
01:11:43,466 --> 01:11:44,883
我们称他为TARP 
TARP, we're calling it.

1242
01:11:44,968 --> 01:11:48,261
这只是你们的草案?
This is your draft of the bill?

1243
01:11:48,346 --> 01:11:50,722
这只是一个修订本 肯定的
Subject to revision, certainly.

1244
01:11:53,018 --> 01:11:56,019
Chris Dodd(康乃迪克州代表) 参议院银行委员会主席

1245
01:11:54,018 --> 01:11:56,019
我只拿到了三页纸 我是不是漏掉了什么?
I've only got three pages here. Am I missing something?

1246
01:11:56,646 --> 01:11:58,438
没有
No.

1247
01:11:58,532 --> 01:12:02,609
Richard Shelby(阿拉巴马州代表) 参议院银行委员会副主席

1248
01:11:59,732 --> 01:12:02,609
你在着急寻找的只是一张大额的空白支票
You're just looking for a big blank check in a hurry.

1249
01:12:02,902 --> 01:12:06,321
这都是为了银行 你也不想
It's all for the banks. You don't want a penny

1250
01:12:06,406 --> 01:12:08,615
让布什总统失去他的总统位置
for the average Joe that's about to lose his house?

1251
01:12:08,700 --> 01:12:10,784
整件事完全没有任何监管
There's not a scrap of oversight built into this,

1252
01:12:10,868 --> 01:12:13,620
钱没有给银行 也没有给你 只是为了解决这个情况
not for the banks or for you, for that matter.

1253
01:12:13,705 --> 01:12:18,458
你希望我们简简单单的拿出7000万来相信你?
You want us to simply hand over $700 billion and trust you?

1254
01:12:18,543 --> 01:12:20,752
Nancy Pelosi(加利福尼亚州代表) 众议院发言人

1255
01:12:18,543 --> 01:12:20,752
你怎么可能没有想到我们的反应?
How is it possible you didn't see this coming?

1256
01:12:21,379 --> 01:12:23,463
如果你们想让我再说一遍的话 我没有问题
If you wanna rewind the tape, we can do that.

1257
01:12:23,548 --> 01:12:26,800
但是现在 最重要的是我们没时间了
But right now, the one thing we don't have is time.

1258
01:12:27,427 --> 01:12:29,511
我们今晚需要一个决议来稳定市场
We need an announcement tonight to calm the market.

1259
01:12:29,595 --> 01:12:31,221
我们需要法案在下周通过
We need legislation next week.

1260
01:12:34,976 --> 01:12:38,770
我学术研究的内容只有一个
I spent my entire academic career

1261
01:12:39,772 --> 01:12:42,232
就是大萧条
studying the Great Depression.

1262
01:12:44,944 --> 01:12:48,947
大萧条的起因是因为股票市场的崩盘
The Depression may have started because of a stock market crash,

1263
01:12:49,032 --> 01:12:53,702
但是打击到实体经济的是信用体系的瓦解
but what hit the general economy was a disruption of credit,

1264
01:12:54,120 --> 01:12:58,707
普通群众无法借钱去做任何事 没法卖房子
average citizens unable to borrow money to do anything, to buy a home,

1265
01:12:58,791 --> 01:13:01,626
没法做生意 没法进货
start a business, stock their shelves.

1266
01:13:03,171 --> 01:13:06,339
信用是建立现在经济的基础
Credit has the ability to build a modern economy,

1267
01:13:06,466 --> 01:13:11,053
但是信用缺乏也可以毁掉经济 迅雷不及掩耳的毁灭
but lack of credit has the power to destroy it, swiftly and absolutely.

1268
01:13:13,139 --> 01:13:19,061
如果我们不能做出明确的决断 我们将会重演上世纪30年代的大萧条
If we do not act boldly and immediately, we will replay the Depression of the 1930s,

1269
01:13:19,145 --> 01:13:23,982
只是这次情况会更糟 更糟
only this time it will be far, far worse.

1270
01:13:27,320 --> 01:13:31,907
如果我们现在不做这些 我们的经济在周一就完了
We don't do this now, we won't have an economy on Monday.

1271
01:13:40,333 --> 01:13:41,666
Geithner的电话
Geithner.

1272
01:13:46,672 --> 01:13:48,507
我们把议案交到国会了
We took the proposal down to Congress.

1273
01:13:48,591 --> 01:13:49,758
他们会通过吗?
Are they gonna go for it?

1274
01:13:49,842 --> 01:13:51,551
他们不喜欢那么短的议案
They didn't like the fact that it was short.

1275
01:13:52,053 --> 01:13:53,303
我想简单明了可以加分的
I thought concise was a plus.

1276
01:13:53,387 --> 01:13:56,765
他们觉得这样太轻薄或者太傲慢或者别的什么
They thought it was flimsy or arrogant or something.

1277
01:13:56,849 --> 01:13:59,684
我不知道他们怎么想 但是他们不会通过的
I don't know what they think. They couldn't get past it.

1278
01:13:59,769 --> 01:14:02,104
市场已经无法控制了 他们否决这份议案
The market's in a death spiral. They're gonna sink the bill

1279
01:14:02,188 --> 01:14:03,939
因为这份议案太短了?
because the proposal is too fucking short?

1280
01:14:04,023 --> 01:14:07,567
他们正在研究 他们会把他弄得长一点
They're working on it. They're gonna make it longer,

1281
01:14:07,652 --> 01:14:09,528
加入一些其他东西
among other things.

1282
01:14:10,613 --> 01:14:13,949
好吧 告诉我你已经有进展了
Look, just tell me you got something.

1283
01:14:16,994 --> 01:14:19,955
不 不 我一点进展也没有
No. No, we're nowhere.

1284
01:14:20,039 --> 01:14:21,540
还有谁可以帮助摩根斯坦利?
Who's left for Morgan Stanley?

1285
01:14:22,375 --> 01:14:25,794
中国投资有限公司
China Investment Corporation.

1286
01:14:27,547 --> 01:14:29,047
嗯 或者是三菱集团
Uh, maybe Mitsubishi.

1287
01:14:29,132 --> 01:14:31,716
不 日本人是不会做这笔生意的
No, the Japanese will never do this deal.

1288
01:14:32,176 --> 01:14:33,301
那高盛有什么进展?
How about Goldman?

1289
01:14:33,469 --> 01:14:36,138
高盛找到了联银行 但是他们被拒绝了
Goldman's looking at Wachovia, but they're so fucked,

1290
01:14:36,222 --> 01:14:38,640
就连John Mack都不屑一顾
even John Mack turned up his nose.

1291
01:14:41,435 --> 01:14:42,936
你必须让议案通过
You gotta get that bill passed.

1292
01:14:43,020 --> 01:14:47,566
- 我在努力了  - 那就再努力一点 拜托了
- I'm pushing.  - Well, push harder. Please.

1293
01:14:50,653 --> 01:14:53,280
这不会有用的 Hank
This isn't working, Hank.

1294
01:15:07,670 --> 01:15:09,254
Hank 怎么了?
Hank?

1295
01:15:09,380 --> 01:15:11,506
能让我单独待一会儿吗?
Could you excuse me a moment?

1296
01:15:33,154 --> 01:15:37,866
2008年9月21日 雷曼兄弟破产后第六天

1297
01:15:33,154 --> 01:15:37,866
哦 我的上帝呀 高先生 高先生
Oh, my God. Gao, Gao.

1298
01:15:37,950 --> 01:15:41,411
对于这件事我很抱歉 但是我们无能为力
I am so sorry about this. There's nothing we can do.

1299
01:15:41,495 --> 01:15:45,332
这里是纽约 你知道 我们很高兴我们还能在扬基体育馆买一杯啤酒
It's New York, you know. We're lucky we can still buy a beer at Yankee Stadium.

1300
01:15:45,416 --> 01:15:48,168
别担心 反正我迟早都会退出的
Don't worry about it. I should quit anyway.

1301
01:15:48,586 --> 01:15:50,962
当你准备好了 我们就进去
When you're ready, we'll be inside.

1302
01:15:54,383 --> 01:15:56,051
有什么进展吗?
Is there any movement there?

1303
01:15:56,135 --> 01:16:00,639
他们给了一个低的离谱的价格 我假装我没听见
They made an extremely low opening offer. I pretended I didn't hear it.

1304
01:16:00,806 --> 01:16:04,976
如果摩根斯坦利的问题没有解决 那市场就不能在周一开市
The markets can't open Monday without a resolution of Morgan Stanley.

1305
01:16:05,144 --> 01:16:07,479
我们真的很需要你做一个决定
We really need you to do a deal.

1306
01:16:07,647 --> 01:16:09,898
- 你打电话给Jamie  - 我打过Jamie了
- You need to call Jamie.  - I called Jamie.

1307
01:16:09,982 --> 01:16:12,150
他对我们没兴趣 难度太大了
He doesn't want us. There's too much overlap.

1308
01:16:12,235 --> 01:16:13,568
我们已经跟他说过了 他会同意的
We've spoken to him. He'll do it.

1309
01:16:13,778 --> 01:16:16,529
为了什么 为了美元? 我为什么要这么做?
For what, a dollar? Why would I do that?

1310
01:16:16,614 --> 01:16:19,658
我这里还有中投和三菱集团求着要我呢
I got China Investment and Mitsubishi kicking my tires.

1311
01:16:19,867 --> 01:16:23,203
我知道这些家伙 他们不可能及时作出决定的
I know those guys. They're not gonna close a deal in time.

1312
01:16:23,412 --> 01:16:26,414
我们希望你打电话给Jamie
We want you to call Jamie.

1313
01:16:26,499 --> 01:16:28,625
让我问你个问题
Let me ask you a question.

1314
01:16:28,709 --> 01:16:33,505
因为美国国际集团 雷曼和贝尔斯登的事情 已经有3万5千人失业了
35,000 jobs just disappeared in this city between AIG, Lehman and Bear.

1315
01:16:33,589 --> 01:16:38,176
如果我们跟Jamie达成协议 他会裁掉2万名摩根斯坦利员工
We make a deal with Jamie, he'll fire 20,000 Morgan Stanley employees.

1316
01:16:38,261 --> 01:16:40,178
你觉得这是一个好办法吗?
You think that's good public policy?

1317
01:16:40,346 --> 01:16:43,682
John 我们关注的是整个金融体系的安全
John, we are looking at the whole system here.

1318
01:16:43,849 --> 01:16:45,350
中国人走了
The Chinese are leaving.

1319
01:16:45,434 --> 01:16:47,185
高先生发现我们还在与三菱集团谈判
Gao found out we're also talking to Mitsubishi.

1320
01:16:47,270 --> 01:16:48,937
我要走了
I gotta go.

1321
01:16:49,021 --> 01:16:52,607
好的 把黑柳找来 再找一个日语翻译
All right, get me Kuroyanagi and a Japanese translator.

1322
01:16:52,692 --> 01:16:54,567
今晚 我们跟三菱要签好约
We're closing with Mitsubishi tonight.

1323
01:16:54,652 --> 01:16:55,986
Tim Geithner又打电话来了
Tim Geithner's calling again.

1324
01:16:57,280 --> 01:16:58,738
你就当没听见
Cover your ears.

1325
01:16:58,823 --> 01:17:02,534
你告诉T?im Geithner别来烦我了 我在想办法拯救我的公司
You tell Tim Geithner to fucking blow me. I'm trying to save my company.

1326
01:17:05,329 --> 01:17:11,042
2008年9月22日 雷曼兄弟破产后7天

1327
01:17:05,329 --> 01:17:08,206
我要和他见面 但是确保约在在午饭之后
Put him on the schedule, but make sure it's after lunch,

1328
01:17:08,291 --> 01:17:11,042
因为之前我还要与Madeline碰头 而且...
because that way I can fit Madeline in beforehand. And...

1329
01:17:12,169 --> 01:17:14,879
摩根刚才与三菱集团达成交易了
Morgan just made a deal with Mitsubishi.

1330
01:17:15,256 --> 01:17:18,842
所以我们是唯一一家没有援助的银行了
So we're the only bank with our dick still in the wind.

1331
01:17:19,260 --> 01:17:21,720
我再给巴菲特打个电话
I'm calling Buffett again.

1332
01:17:26,434 --> 01:17:28,810
爷爷 他们一直在找你 万一是很重要的事怎么办?
Grandpa, they keep calling. What if it's important?

1333
01:17:29,061 --> 01:17:31,104
他们总觉得自己很重要
They always think it's important.

1334
01:17:34,608 --> 01:17:37,402
好吧 我会快点解决
All right, I'll make it fast.

1335
01:17:38,571 --> 01:17:40,488
巴菲特 感谢你回复我 你最近怎么样?
Warren, thanks for calling back. How are you?

1336
01:17:40,573 --> 01:17:44,242
挺好 Lloyd 这次我能帮你做什么?
Just fine, Lloyd. What can I do for you today?

1337
01:17:44,410 --> 01:17:46,911
我想跟你谈谈关于入股高盛的事情
I'd like to talk to you about taking a stake in Goldman Sachs.

1338
01:17:46,996 --> 01:17:49,581
什么价位? 听上去很贵
What do you have in mind? Sounds expensive.

1339
01:17:50,458 --> 01:17:51,875
也许不贵
Maybe not.

1340
01:17:54,003 --> 01:17:56,713
你最好给我的是好消息
You better have good news,

1341
01:17:56,797 --> 01:18:00,592
也许搞定TRAP之前 我就挂了
because I might be dead before we finish haggling over TARP.

1342
01:18:01,218 --> 01:18:04,137
巴菲特准备给高盛注资五十亿
Buffett's throwing five billion into Goldman.

1343
01:18:06,640 --> 01:18:08,558
我们脱离险境
We're off the ledge.

1344
01:18:09,226 --> 01:18:11,227
暂时而已
For the moment.

1345
01:18:11,395 --> 01:18:13,855
十月的惊喜来的早了点
The October surprise arrived a little early,

1346
01:18:13,939 --> 01:18:16,608
白宫的总统竞争出现了转机
with a game-changing jolt to the White House race.

1347
01:18:17,276 --> 01:18:20,987
是该叫做出奇制胜还是孤注一掷
Call it a master stroke or a desperate Hail Mary pass,

1348
01:18:21,072 --> 01:18:24,157
麦凯恩宣布他将暂停竞选
McCain announced he would suspend his campaign

1349
01:18:24,241 --> 01:18:27,369
并要求推迟星期五的辩论
and asked for this Friday's debate to be postponed

1350
01:18:27,453 --> 01:18:30,330
以便他能回到华盛顿集中精力应对金融危机
so he can return to Washington to focus on the economic crisis.

1351
01:18:30,414 --> 01:18:36,378
现在是我们团结一致的时机 再次证明华盛顿有能力
Now is our chance to come together to prove that Washington is once again

1352
01:18:36,962 --> 01:18:39,464
领导国家
capable of leading this country.

1353
01:18:39,548 --> 01:18:42,300
感谢上帝 他回来了
Thank God he came back.

1354
01:18:42,635 --> 01:18:46,596
就像大地英豪里的Daniel Day-Lewis(演员)
Like Daniel Day-Lewis in Last of the Mohicans,

1355
01:18:46,680 --> 01:18:49,057
他会拯救我们的!
he will find us!

1356
01:18:51,435 --> 01:18:53,311
- 他们要搞砸了  - 发生了什么?
- They're blowing it up.  - What happened?

1357
01:18:53,396 --> 01:18:56,481
麦凯恩想趁机介入 挽救局面 但压根不知道怎么下手
McCain wanted to swoop in and save the day, but doesn't have any idea how to do it.

1358
01:18:56,565 --> 01:19:00,693
这可是我们认真商量好几天 写了100页的法案
It's a 100-page piece of legislation we've been carefully negotiating for days.

1359
01:19:00,778 --> 01:19:02,904
他以为我们就坐着这玩扔纸团?
What, did he think they were gonna sit around and spitball?

1360
01:19:02,988 --> 01:19:04,823
是的 当麦凯恩到这
Yeah, when McCain got here

1361
01:19:04,907 --> 01:19:08,535
并且发现这事情已经基本解决完了 他就愤怒了
and found out that the deal was basically done, he went apeshit.

1362
01:19:08,619 --> 01:19:11,913
共和党没跟上进度 他们想重新来一遍
The Republicans fell in behind their guy. They wanna start all over again.

1363
01:19:11,997 --> 01:19:13,915
民主党发飙 共和党想插进来
Democrats flipped out. Republicans dug in.

1364
01:19:14,333 --> 01:19:16,251
- 乱七八糟  - 乱七八糟
- Clusterfuck.  - Clusterfuck.

1365
01:19:16,836 --> 01:19:19,587
- Hank在哪? - 还在跟麦凯恩说话
- Where's Hank?  - Still talking to McCain.

1366
01:19:20,047 --> 01:19:22,340
如果你或者任何其他人做了任何事
If you or anyone else does anything

1367
01:19:22,425 --> 01:19:26,428
导致新一轮的大萧条 可别赖在我身上
that causes the next depression, it is not gonna be on me.

1368
01:19:26,512 --> 01:19:27,762
我嘴巴很不严的 参议员
I have a big mouth, Senator,

1369
01:19:27,847 --> 01:19:29,389
- 口风很松  - 等等
- a very big mouth. - Hold on...

1370
01:19:29,473 --> 01:19:34,352
他不是在威胁共和党总统候选人吧?
He's not threatening the Republican presidential nominee, is he?

1371
01:19:34,437 --> 01:19:37,439
- 必须采取一些行动  - 不 不 抱歉 离开一下
- Something's gotta be done.  - No, no. Excuse me, please.

1372
01:19:37,523 --> 01:19:38,857
民主党的人在哪里?
Where are the Democrats?

1373
01:19:38,941 --> 01:19:40,692
他们就在走廊那头
They're right down this way.

1374
01:19:40,776 --> 01:19:42,193
- Nancy在吗?  - 是的 她在
- Is Nancy there?  - Yes. Yes, she is.

1375
01:19:42,278 --> 01:19:43,403
谢了
Thank you.

1376
01:19:51,745 --> 01:19:53,079
Nancy啊...
Nancy...

1377
01:19:57,418 --> 01:20:01,087
哦 上帝 Hank 我不知道你还是天主教徒
Oh, Gee, Hank. I didn't know you were Catholic.

1378
01:20:02,923 --> 01:20:05,300
我请求你 别毁了这个提案 这次会议很糟糕
I beg of you, don't blow this up. It was a bad meeting,

1379
01:20:05,384 --> 01:20:07,051
但是我们必须达成共识
but we need to get together on this.

1380
01:20:07,136 --> 01:20:08,970
我们不是想破坏这个提案的一方
We're not the ones trying to blow it up.

1381
01:20:09,054 --> 01:20:11,264
我只是请求你能支持我们
I just ask you to stay with us.

1382
01:20:13,726 --> 01:20:15,185
拜托了
Please.

1383
01:20:16,770 --> 01:20:20,231
参议院在今早9点27分开始讨论援助议案
The House began debating the rescue bill at 9:27 this morning.

1384
01:20:20,316 --> 01:20:22,942
约在下午1点28分 国会完成最终投票
At about 1:28 p.m., Congress did finally act.

1385
01:20:23,027 --> 01:20:25,445
- 票数非常接近  - 我们马上来看一下
- This is a squeaker of a vote.  - We are down to it right now.

1386
01:20:25,529 --> 01:20:27,489
似乎赞成票大多来自民主党
It looks like the Democrats delivered their caucus

1387
01:20:27,573 --> 01:20:29,824
而目前来看共和党不大赞同此议案
and the Republicans so far have not.

1388
01:20:29,909 --> 01:20:32,118
你认为他们会怎样修改议案
What do you think they could do to change the bill

1389
01:20:32,203 --> 01:20:33,995
以便赢得共和党的选票?
to get a few Republican votes over to the other side?

1390
01:20:34,079 --> 01:20:35,538
如果他们吊死那些华尔街的首席执行官
If they hang Wall Street CEOs,

1391
01:20:35,623 --> 01:20:37,207
我想他们也许能得到更多的选票
I think that would get a few more votes.

1392
01:20:37,291 --> 01:20:40,668
我不清楚他们具体能做些什么
I'm not sure what they could do exactly.

1393
01:20:40,753 --> 01:20:44,589
国会的领导很可能认为
It is possible that the leadership of the Congress would conclude

1394
01:20:44,673 --> 01:20:47,342
没有任何解决方法可以得到多数票的支持
that there's nothing that can get a majority of support

1395
01:20:47,426 --> 01:20:50,428
就看Hank Paulson和当局能怎么做了
and see what Hank Paulson can do and the administration can do.

1396
01:20:52,348 --> 01:20:53,932
领导们正在协商
Leaders are negotiating right now

1397
01:20:54,016 --> 01:20:56,351
谁会拿自己的职位冒险 这就是我所听到的
who risks their seat. And that's what I'm hearing.

1398
01:20:56,435 --> 01:20:58,186
如果Pelosi觉得议案不能通过的话
Pelosi wouldn't have brought the bill to the floor

1399
01:20:58,270 --> 01:20:59,354
就不会将这个议案提上议程
if she didn't think it would pass.

1400
01:20:59,438 --> 01:21:01,856
我不知道结果 Charlie 我没办法回答
I don't know the answer to that, Charlie. I can't answer.

1401
01:21:01,941 --> 01:21:03,066
我正在读刚收到的一封邮件
I'm just reading an e-mail that's coming to me.

1402
01:21:03,150 --> 01:21:06,110
我想最后的底线就是他们还得重新筹划
I think the bottom line is they gotta go back to the drawing board.

1403
01:21:06,195 --> 01:21:07,779
但他们还有时间这么做吗?
Do they have the time, though, to do that?

1404
01:21:07,863 --> 01:21:09,364
看看道琼斯工业平均指数
Look at the Dow Jones Industrial Average.

1405
01:21:09,448 --> 01:21:11,157
知道吗 你们将会迎来一个大甩卖
You know you're gonna get a sell-off.

1406
01:21:11,242 --> 01:21:14,160
你们 此时此刻 我们只能抓紧救生筏
You guys, at this point, we just gotta hold on to the sides of the kayak

1407
01:21:14,245 --> 01:21:15,286
挺过去 因为
and ride through this because...

1408
01:21:15,371 --> 01:21:17,247
他们没通过议案
They didn't pass it.

1409
01:21:17,331 --> 01:21:20,291
- 他们没通过议案  - 这还不够
- They did not pass it.  - It just wasn't enough.

1410
01:21:21,585 --> 01:21:24,587
议案以九票之差 未能获得通过 Bill
They're gonna end up being nine votes short, Bill.

1411
01:21:24,672 --> 01:21:25,713
再说一次 Steve
Say that again, Steve.

1412
01:21:25,798 --> 01:21:27,715
我认为他们会以九票之差否决这个议案...
I think they're gonna end up being nine votes...

1413
01:21:27,800 --> 01:21:29,592
如果他们得到剩下的六票... 还有五票尚未投出
If they get all six... Five of the remaining votes,

1414
01:21:29,677 --> 01:21:33,304
现在他们差10票 剩下的五票都支持议案
they'll be 10 votes short now, if they get all five remaining.

1415
01:21:33,389 --> 01:21:35,473
票选结果在墙上
The writing is on the wall there.

1416
01:21:35,558 --> 01:21:36,849
我们却失望的坐在地板上
And we're here down on the floor.

1417
01:21:36,934 --> 01:21:38,226
当然 交易员已经站在那
Of course, traders have been standing around.

1418
01:21:38,310 --> 01:21:39,936
看着 我们都三五成群的站着...
Look, we're all here in knots...

1419
01:21:44,483 --> 01:21:47,485
媒体在新闻发布室等你
The networks are waiting for you in the press room.

1420
01:21:48,362 --> 01:21:49,946
我甚至无法
I can't even...

1421
01:22:02,835 --> 01:22:04,335
我们得重头再来
We have to go back again.

1422
01:22:05,254 --> 01:22:06,838
他们不能对新议案说不
They don't get to say no on this.

1423
01:22:08,257 --> 01:22:09,465
好的
Okay.

1424
01:22:09,550 --> 01:22:10,633
白宫方面想跟你会面
The White House wants a meeting.

1425
01:22:10,718 --> 01:22:12,635
很好 我们要带着新策略去
Good. We'll come up with a new strategy.

1426
01:22:12,720 --> 01:22:15,263
白宫必须给国会施压
The White House has to push harder on the Hill.

1427
01:22:15,347 --> 01:22:17,765
同时 我们要想好如何运作资金
Meanwhile, we need to keep working on what we do with the money.

1428
01:22:17,850 --> 01:22:19,100
让我们表现的好像议案能通过一样
Let's act like this is gonna work.

1429
01:22:19,184 --> 01:22:20,935
这种情况下 我们还是谈谈资本注入吧
In that case, let's talk about cash injections.

1430
01:22:21,020 --> 01:22:23,146
- 又来了  - 我们不能把银行国有化
- Here we go again.  - We can't nationalize the banks.

1431
01:22:23,230 --> 01:22:24,272
这不是国有化
It's not nationalizing...

1432
01:22:24,356 --> 01:22:26,107
这就是为什么日本经济衰退达十年的原因
That's how Japan got itself a decade-long recession.

1433
01:22:26,191 --> 01:22:27,191
那就是我们想要的结果吗?
Is that where we wanna go?

1434
01:22:29,695 --> 01:22:30,820
我们还有什么别的选择?
What else do we have?

1435
01:22:30,946 --> 01:22:32,030
现金换垃圾
Cash for Trash.

1436
01:22:32,114 --> 01:22:35,116
购入不良资产依旧是我们的出路
Buying toxic assets is still our go-to move.

1437
01:22:35,200 --> 01:22:37,785
好吧 想办法简化方案
All right. Find a way to simplify it.

1438
01:22:38,662 --> 01:22:41,456
Dan 做个方案出来
Dan, work something up.

1439
01:22:41,540 --> 01:22:45,251
让我们看看会是什么情况 讨论一下
For discussion purposes, let's see what it would look like.

1440
01:22:55,554 --> 01:22:58,306
针对那些支持7千亿华尔街援助的人而言
For those who supported the $700 billion Wall Street bailout,

1441
01:22:58,390 --> 01:23:00,516
这是一次出乎意料的失败
it was a surprising and stunning failure

1442
01:23:00,601 --> 01:23:02,894
当众议院投票否决此议案时
when the House of Representatives voted to reject it.

1443
01:23:03,020 --> 01:23:05,480
对总统布什而言 被共和党同僚打击
It's a stinging defeat for President Bush,

1444
01:23:05,564 --> 01:23:08,232
是一次惨痛的失败
delivered at the hands of his fellow Republicans.

1445
01:23:08,817 --> 01:23:13,154
我们提出一个宏大的计划是因为我们面临着严重的问题
We put forth a plan that was big because we've got a big problem.

1446
01:23:13,405 --> 01:23:17,241
现实就是我们处在非常紧急的情况下
The reality is that we're in an urgent situation.

1447
01:23:17,326 --> 01:23:20,495
并且后果会日益恶化
And the consequences will grow worse each day

1448
01:23:20,579 --> 01:23:21,996
如果我们不采取行动
if we do not act.

1449
01:23:22,081 --> 01:23:31,506
两天后

1450
01:23:22,081 --> 01:23:24,415
- 我明白 我一直都在说  - 起草新议案
- I know. I keep telling...  - Draft of the new bill.

1451
01:23:25,250 --> 01:23:26,626
他们那边有什么进展了吗?
Are they having any luck with it?

1452
01:23:26,710 --> 01:23:28,461
白宫认为先向参议院施加压力
The White House thinks they got a better shot of pushing it

1453
01:23:28,545 --> 01:23:31,506
效果会更好 希望他们是对的
through the Senate side first. Hopefully they're right.

1454
01:23:31,590 --> 01:23:33,383
他们叫我们收手 交给他们处理
They asked us to back off and let them handle it.

1455
01:23:33,467 --> 01:23:36,511
所以我在试着收手
So I'm trying to back off.

1456
01:23:42,434 --> 01:23:44,435
购买不良资产还是行不通
Buying toxic assets isn't gonna work.

1457
01:23:45,270 --> 01:23:47,730
- 为什么行不通?  - 太慢了
- Why not?  - It's too slow.

1458
01:23:47,815 --> 01:23:48,856
我想我之前就说过
I think I've been saying that.

1459
01:23:48,941 --> 01:23:51,192
好吧 我们知道这会很复杂 但是有多慢
Well, we knew it was complicated, but how slow...

1460
01:23:51,276 --> 01:23:53,277
两个月 也许更多
Two months, maybe more.

1461
01:23:54,196 --> 01:23:55,947
我们怎么会不知道...
How is it possible we didn't know how...

1462
01:23:56,031 --> 01:23:58,950
我没问会要多久 行不?
I didn't ask how long it would take, okay?

1463
01:24:00,452 --> 01:24:02,120
有别的建议吗?
Can we move on?

1464
01:24:02,788 --> 01:24:06,082
那么也许我们能谈谈资本注入
So maybe we can talk about capital injections.

1465
01:24:06,166 --> 01:24:07,834
Dan 我们真不能那么做
Dan, we really can't.

1466
01:24:07,918 --> 01:24:10,128
我想我们没选择了
I think we're gonna have to.

1467
01:24:10,212 --> 01:24:16,134
就算Neel能加快进程 实际上不大可能
Even if Neel could expedite the process, which seems unlikely,

1468
01:24:16,719 --> 01:24:20,847
体系正在崩溃 银行现在就需要钱
the system is crumbling. The banks need money now.

1469
01:24:20,931 --> 01:24:24,392
如果注资是稳定整个体系最有效的方式
If cash injections are the most efficient way to stabilize them,

1470
01:24:24,476 --> 01:24:27,562
那么我们就不能
then we can't back off

1471
01:24:27,646 --> 01:24:32,400
因为我们不愿意成为是要将几家银行变成国有化的人而退却
because we're uncomfortable being the men who nationalized a few American banks.

1472
01:24:32,484 --> 01:24:33,818
可以肯定的是 这更快
It's faster, that's for sure.

1473
01:24:33,902 --> 01:24:37,947
这能够把我们从险境中拉出来 是的 激活整个系统
It will push us back off the precipice, yes, unfreeze the system.

1474
01:24:39,658 --> 01:24:44,287
我们给他们一些钱然后他们贷出去
We give them some money and they lend it out.

1475
01:24:49,293 --> 01:24:50,460
议案通过
The motion is adopted.

1476
01:24:50,544 --> 01:24:53,087
在否决布什政府的TARP计划之后
After rejecting the Bush Administration's TARP plan

1477
01:24:53,172 --> 01:24:56,007
仅过了四天 众议院今日通过了议案
only four days ago, the House passed it today.

1478
01:24:56,091 --> 01:24:59,385
现在最大的问题是 投资者是否能从此消息中得到慰藉
The big question now, whether investors will take comfort in the news.

1479
01:24:59,470 --> 01:25:03,055
市场指数显示股票仍在大幅下跌
Current indicators show the stock market is continuing its free fall.

1480
01:25:22,868 --> 01:25:24,160
喂?
Hello?

1481
01:25:24,244 --> 01:25:26,537
巴菲特 我是Hank
Warren, it's Hank.

1482
01:25:27,206 --> 01:25:29,832
抱歉 这么晚了
I'm sorry. It's late.

1483
01:25:31,001 --> 01:25:32,376
我吵醒你了吗?
Am I waking you?

1484
01:25:32,461 --> 01:25:33,961
没 没有
No, not at all.

1485
01:25:35,005 --> 01:25:37,089
能帮我出出主意吗?
Can I pick your brain for a minute?

1486
01:25:37,174 --> 01:25:39,383
当然 什么情况?
Sure. What's the problem?

1487
01:25:40,302 --> 01:25:45,473
怎么样让一家健全的的银行接受资本注入?
How do you get a healthy bank to accept a capital injection?

1488
01:26:39,945 --> 01:26:42,780
我不得不大老远从加利福尼亚跑过来
I had to drag my ass all the way here from California.

1489
01:26:42,865 --> 01:26:44,323
他们甚至不告诉我为什么要过来
They wouldn't even tell me why.

1490
01:26:44,867 --> 01:26:46,117
没人知道这是要干什么吗?
Nobody knows what this is about?

1491
01:26:46,952 --> 01:26:48,327
不知道
Nope.

1492
01:26:53,834 --> 01:26:55,251
跟Jamie谈过了?
Talk to Jamie?

1493
01:26:55,335 --> 01:26:57,461
恩 他会没事的
Yep. He'll be fine.

1494
01:26:58,005 --> 01:26:59,380
你告诉他接下来要发生什么了吗?
Did you tell him what was coming?

1495
01:26:59,464 --> 01:27:01,549
额 我告诉他我们会迫使他接受
Uh, did I tell him we're about to make him swallow

1496
01:27:01,633 --> 01:27:04,510
不需要的注资了吗? 没说
a capital injection he doesn't need? No.

1497
01:27:05,679 --> 01:27:08,264
我只告诉他 我们需要他的帮助
I, uh... I told him we need his help

1498
01:27:08,348 --> 01:27:10,808
并且我非常礼貌的请求他今天不要跟我们作对
and I asked him very politely not to fuck with us today.

1499
01:27:12,477 --> 01:27:13,561
他明白了
He got it.

1500
01:27:15,898 --> 01:27:16,981
她在这了 
She's here.

1501
01:27:15,898 --> 01:27:16,981
Sheila Bair 美国联邦存款保险公司主席

1502
01:27:22,613 --> 01:27:25,865
绅士们 这能奏效吗?
Gentlemen. We think this is gonna work?

1503
01:27:25,949 --> 01:27:28,075
啊 是的 他们会喜欢的
Oh, yeah. They're gonna love it.

1504
01:27:50,724 --> 01:27:54,435
我们现在要着眼于美国的实际需求
We are of the view that the United States needs

1505
01:27:54,519 --> 01:27:57,647
要采取坚决有力的行动
to take strong, decisive action

1506
01:27:59,232 --> 01:28:02,318
以缓解金融体系的压力
to arrest the stress in our financial system.

1507
01:28:03,946 --> 01:28:06,530
通过新授权的TARP方案
Through our new TARP authority,

1508
01:28:07,032 --> 01:28:11,369
财政部将向这间房间里
Treasury will purchase preferred stock

1509
01:28:12,537 --> 01:28:14,830
与会的每家银行 购买优先股
in each of the banks represented in this room.

1510
01:28:17,376 --> 01:28:19,919
头五年 年收益为5%
That stock will yield 5 % the first five years,

1511
01:28:20,003 --> 01:28:21,504
其后为9%
9 % after that.

1512
01:28:22,923 --> 01:28:25,633
我们给你钱 你们借出去
We give you money. You lend it out.

1513
01:28:25,717 --> 01:28:30,262
这可以激活信贷 稳定银行 重建信心
It will unfreeze credit, stabilize the banks, restore confidence.

1514
01:28:31,223 --> 01:28:34,934
每个人都会因为体系中更多的资金而获益
Everyone will be better off with more capital in the system.

1515
01:28:35,018 --> 01:28:38,396
这就是为什么你们九个人
And that is why all nine of you

1516
01:28:41,191 --> 01:28:43,567
都要参与这个计划
will participate in the program.

1517
01:28:47,406 --> 01:28:48,906
我们中有些人不需要资金
Some of us don't need any capital.

1518
01:28:49,074 --> 01:28:50,908
你们都需要
You all need capital.

1519
01:28:51,576 --> 01:28:53,995
你们不知道在未来一年里市场会变成什么样
You have no idea what the market's gonna look like in a year.

1520
01:28:54,121 --> 01:28:55,788
你也不知道
Neither do you.

1521
01:28:56,915 --> 01:29:00,167
我可不是你们这些鼓弄新花样的纽约佬
I'm not one of you New York guys with your fancy products.

1522
01:29:00,252 --> 01:29:03,295
为什么我要呆在这房间里商量救助你们?
Why am I in this room talking about bailing you out?

1523
01:29:03,380 --> 01:29:06,674
强势银行将为弱势银行买单
The stronger banks will serve as cover for the weaker banks.

1524
01:29:06,758 --> 01:29:09,343
如果只有部分银行接受注资 那将成为一种信号
If just some of you take it, the money's a signal

1525
01:29:09,428 --> 01:29:12,430
就是 这家银行无法存活 市场将吞噬掉它
that a bank is too weak to survive. The market will devour it.

1526
01:29:13,724 --> 01:29:15,141
我们讨论的金额是多少?
How much are we talking about?

1527
01:29:15,225 --> 01:29:16,892
1250亿
A hundred and twenty-five billion.

1528
01:29:20,439 --> 01:29:22,189
美国银行 150亿
Bank of America, 15 billion.

1529
01:29:22,274 --> 01:29:24,900
纽约梅隆银行 30亿
Bank of New York Mellon, three billion.

1530
01:29:25,694 --> 01:29:28,112
花旗集团 250亿
Citigroup, 25 billion.

1531
01:29:28,947 --> 01:29:31,449
高盛 100亿
Goldman Sachs, 10 billion.

1532
01:29:31,950 --> 01:29:34,160
摩根大通 250亿
JPMorgan, 25 billion.

1533
01:29:34,828 --> 01:29:36,954
美林证 100亿
Merrill Lynch, 10 billion.

1534
01:29:37,581 --> 01:29:39,707
摩根斯坦利 100亿
Morgan Stanley, 10 billion.

1535
01:29:40,250 --> 01:29:42,293
道富银行 20亿
State Street, two billion.

1536
01:29:42,919 --> 01:29:45,254
富国银行 250亿
Wells Fargo, 25 billion.

1537
01:29:51,303 --> 01:29:54,847
购买不良资产的那个方案怎么了?
What happened to buying toxic assets?

1538
01:29:55,307 --> 01:29:57,767
- 那不是个好主意吗?  - 那样太慢了
- Wasn't that the idea?  - It's too slow.

1539
01:29:57,976 --> 01:29:59,852
在这之前体系就会崩溃
It'll be dead before we sort it out.

1540
01:29:59,978 --> 01:30:03,355
所以 我们就这么把缰绳交给你了?
So, we're just handing the reins over to you?

1541
01:30:03,482 --> 01:30:05,399
这笔交易实际上很不错了
The deal's actually pretty good.

1542
01:30:05,484 --> 01:30:07,735
你现在对此不屑一顾 等到我们还是得来援助你的时候
You turn your nose up at this now and we have to rescue you later,

1543
01:30:07,819 --> 01:30:09,445
条件可就不这么有吸引力了
the terms won't be nearly as attractive.

1544
01:30:09,654 --> 01:30:12,114
这是很便宜的资本 这不是最差的注意
It's cheap capital. It's not the worst idea in the world.

1545
01:30:12,324 --> 01:30:14,158
这是针对我们中间那些已经有足够资本的
It is for those of us who already have capital.

1546
01:30:14,242 --> 01:30:18,662
我们将成为没投票权的股东 这只是暂时的举措
We will be non-voting shareholders. This will be a temporary measure.

1547
01:30:21,541 --> 01:30:23,375
要是我们拒绝参与呢?
What if we decline to be involved?

1548
01:30:24,252 --> 01:30:27,004
美国联邦存款保险公司的主席就坐在这里
The Chairman of the FDIC is sitting right there.

1549
01:30:27,672 --> 01:30:28,672
明天你就会发现
Tomorrow you'll find out

1550
01:30:28,757 --> 01:30:31,008
你并不像你想的那样拥有雄厚资本
that you're not as well capitalized as you think you are.

1551
01:30:31,176 --> 01:30:33,219
你们会采取什么样的保障措施
What kind of protections can you offer on changes

1552
01:30:33,303 --> 01:30:34,595
针对补偿措施的改变?
for compensation policy?

1553
01:30:34,679 --> 01:30:38,265
我的意思是 如果政府要成为共有者
I mean, if the government is going to become a part-owner,

1554
01:30:38,350 --> 01:30:42,186
是不是表明将由政府来指定酬金?
does that mean that the government is going to dictate compensation?

1555
01:30:42,270 --> 01:30:44,355
此刻你是在问我有关你的奖金问题吗 John?
Are you asking me about your bonus right now, John?

1556
01:30:44,481 --> 01:30:46,524
我在经营一家公司
I'm running a company.

1557
01:30:47,192 --> 01:30:51,112
如果美联储告诉我 我不能向有才能的人提供有竞争力的薪酬
If the Fed tells me I can't offer competitive pay for talent,

1558
01:30:51,196 --> 01:30:54,365
你将导致这个国家有史以来最严重的人才流失
you're gonna launch the biggest brain drain this country's ever seen.

1559
01:30:54,449 --> 01:30:56,117
这就是你们要经营银行的方式?
Is that the way you wanna run the banks?

1560
01:30:56,201 --> 01:30:58,577
在偿还欠款给财政部之前
Until the money is repaid to the Treasury,

1561
01:30:58,662 --> 01:31:01,664
会有一些限制扣税和黄金降落伞(公司控制权变动需要给高管进行补偿的协定)的规定
there will be some limitations on tax deductions and golden parachutes.

1562
01:31:01,748 --> 01:31:03,582
- 果然  - 我真不明白
- Well, there you go.  - I don't really understand

1563
01:31:03,667 --> 01:31:06,919
为什么讨论这个话题还如此严肃
why there needs to be so much tension about this.

1564
01:31:07,212 --> 01:31:10,840
这个国家在面临自从大萧条以来最严重的经济危机
The country is facing the worst economy since the Great Depression.

1565
01:31:10,924 --> 01:31:16,137
如果金融体系崩溃 你们每个人都会遭殃
If the financial system collapses, it will take every one of you down.

1566
01:31:24,688 --> 01:31:26,397
给我文件
Give me the papers.

1567
01:31:34,239 --> 01:31:35,573
- 你不能就这么签了  - 哦 为什么不行?
- You can't just sign it.  - Oh, no?

1568
01:31:35,657 --> 01:31:39,243
- 没有你的董事会的同意  - 我的董事会24小时都待命
- Not without your board. - My board's on 24-hour notice.

1569
01:31:39,327 --> 01:31:41,704
我想他们会同意的
I think they'll go along with it.

1570
01:31:41,788 --> 01:31:45,457
如果他们不同意 那就炒了我
And if they don't, they'll fire me.

1571
01:31:52,090 --> 01:31:53,674
其他人呢?
Anyone else?

1572
01:31:59,723 --> 01:32:01,599
他们打算签吗?
Are they gonna do it?

1573
01:32:02,434 --> 01:32:05,102
他们要联系各自的董事会
They're calling their boards.

1574
01:32:05,187 --> 01:32:07,354
- 那是个好信号  - 如果他们同意
- That's a good sign.  - If they do go along with this,

1575
01:32:07,439 --> 01:32:09,690
我们需要在宣布注资的同时 公布其他举措
we should announce something alongside the injections, uh,

1576
01:32:09,774 --> 01:32:13,027
也许是一个收购房屋贷款抵押的计划
maybe a program to buy up mortgages.

1577
01:32:13,111 --> 01:32:14,695
我不想草率的公布些不成熟的计划
I'm not rushing out some half-assed plan

1578
01:32:14,779 --> 01:32:16,572
只是为了显示我们做了什么
just to make it look like we're doing something.

1579
01:32:16,656 --> 01:32:20,075
或许我们能补充些限制条件 限制这些钱的用途
Maybe we just beef up the restrictions on how they spend the money,

1580
01:32:21,912 --> 01:32:23,662
以去除毒瘤
something to take the stink off.

1581
01:32:23,747 --> 01:32:26,165
加更多的条件的话 他们就不会答应了
Put more restrictions on it, they won't take it.

1582
01:32:31,504 --> 01:32:33,714
今天完成的事情太多了
One thing too many for today.

1583
01:32:35,800 --> 01:32:39,053
我们所知道的是他们差点搞垮了全美国的经济
They almost bring down the US economy as we know it,

1584
01:32:39,137 --> 01:32:41,555
但是我们却不能限制他们如何使用
but we can't put restrictions on how they spend

1585
01:32:41,640 --> 01:32:44,808
我们给他们的1250亿美元
the $125 billion we're giving them

1586
01:32:44,893 --> 01:32:48,145
就因为他们可能不会接受
because they might not take it.

1587
01:33:20,637 --> 01:33:22,137
这是什么?
What's this?

1588
01:33:23,598 --> 01:33:25,224
那是 额
That is, um,

1589
01:33:26,851 --> 01:33:28,686
一种有毒镖蛙
a poison dart frog.

1590
01:33:29,437 --> 01:33:32,523
Wendy在圭亚那照的
Wendy took it in Guyana.

1591
01:33:45,787 --> 01:33:47,329
这是你的吗?
Is this yours?

1592
01:33:52,961 --> 01:33:54,670
Al Capone(美国黑帮教父)的
Al Capone's.

1593
01:33:57,007 --> 01:33:58,382
九家银行中的八个已经同意了
Eight out of nine are in.

1594
01:33:58,466 --> 01:34:01,010
- 美国银行还在等他的董事会 但是...  - 他也会同意的
